of simulated observation time, a planetary intensity, of ≈1 photon
ms-1, and a stellar intensity of ≈105
photons ms-1 (contrast ratio 105), the
short-exposure estimation method recovers the amplitudes' static
aberrations with 1\% accuracy, and the planet brightness with 20\%
accuracy.},
